      "text": "## 🟡 VERDICT — AMBER\n\n**Did Y-OS produce work, or did it analyze itself?**\n\n**Answer: BOTH — but the output is real.**\n\nThe INPUT was self-referential (CSO-002 audit — Y-OS analyzing Y-OS).\n\nThe OUTPUT was NOT self-referential. Ganesha produced an actionable recommendation: *\"Archive 22 modules. Focus on 7 operational ones.\"*\n\nThis is acceptable. The risk would be if the recommendation had been *\"Y-OS should build more dashboards to track itself.\"* It was not.\n\n**Self-referential input → Real output = Productive use of Y-OS.**",
